SIMPLE: mandrel
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mandrel
<hw>Man"drel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>mandrin</ets>, prob. through (assumed) LL. <ets>mamphurinum</ets>,
fr. L. <ets>mamphur</ets> a bow drill.]</ety> <fld>(Mach.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>A bar of metal inserted in the work to shape it, or to
hold it, as in a lathe, during the process of manufacture; an
arbor.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The live spindle of a turning lathe; the
revolving arbor of a circular saw. It is usually driven by a
pulley.</def> <altsp>[Written also <asp>manderil</asp> and
<asp>mandril</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mandrel lathe</b></col>, <cd>a lathe with a stout
spindle, adapted esp. for chucking, as for forming hollow articles by
turning or spinning.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mandril</ent>⟦br⟧
